  <description type="morphology">Plants 0.1–0.3 cm. Stem leaves erect to flexuose when dry, erect when moist, not 3-ranked, ligulate to narrowly lanceolate, 2–4 mm; base not decurrent; margins revolute basally and to near apex, entire; apex obtuse to rounded (to acute in some arctic populations); costa wide, ending just before apex; inner laminal cells larger, walls thinner than marginal cells. Sexual condition usually dioicous. Seta 1.5–5 cm. Capsule 1.5–4 mm. Spores 40–51 µm.</description>
